#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.54:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Sappaññavagga"
msgstr "6. A Wise Person"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 54. Gilānasutta → gilāyanaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Gilānasutta"
msgstr "54. Sick"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:"
msgstr ""
"At that time several mendicants were making a robe for the Buddha, thinking "
"that"

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.3"
msgid "“niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"when his robe was finished and the three months of the rains residence had "
"passed the Buddha would set out wandering."

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.4"
msgid "Assosi kho mahānāmo sakko:"
msgstr "Mahānāma the Sakyan heard about this."

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.5"
msgid "“sambahulā kira bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.6"
msgid "‘niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo "
"sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him "
"that he had heard that the Buddha was leaving. He added:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.8"
msgid "“sutametaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.9"
msgid "‘sambahulā kira bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.10"
msgid "niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: Na kho netaṃ → na kho te etaṃ (si, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.54:1.11"
msgid "Na kho netaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ "
msgstr "“Sir, I haven’t heard and learned it in the presence of the Buddha "

msgctxt "sn55.54:1.12"
msgid ""
"sappaññena upāsakena sappañño upāsako ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno "
"ovaditabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"how a wise lay follower should advise another wise lay follower who is sick, "
"suffering, gravely ill.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Sappaññena, mahānāma, upāsakena sappañño upāsako ābādhiko dukkhito "
"bāḷhagilāno catūhi assāsanīyehi dhammehi assāsetabbo:"
msgstr ""
"“Mahānāma, a wise lay follower should put at ease another wise lay follower "
"who is sick, suffering, gravely ill with four consolations."

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.2"
msgid "‘assāsatāyasmā—"
msgstr "‘Be at ease, sir."

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.3"
msgid ""
"atthāyasmato buddhe aveccappasādo itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā "
"devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr "You have experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.4"
msgid "Assāsatāyasmā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.5"
msgid "atthāyasmato dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.6"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:2.7"
msgid "ariyakantāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikānī’ti."
msgstr ""
"And you have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to "
"immersion.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.409"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sappaññena, mahānāma, upāsakena sappañño upāsako ābādhiko dukkhito "
"bāḷhagilāno imehi catūhi assāsanīyehi dhammehi assāsetvā evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"When a wise lay follower has put at ease another wise lay follower who is "
"sick, suffering, gravely ill with these four consolations, they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.2"
msgid "‘atthāyasmato mātāpitūsu apekkhā’ti?"
msgstr "‘Are you concerned for your mother and father?’"

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.3"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.4"
msgid "‘atthi me mātāpitūsu apekkhā’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I am,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.5"
msgid "‘āyasmā kho māriso maraṇadhammo."
msgstr "‘But sir, it’s your nature to die."

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.6"
msgid "Sacepāyasmā mātāpitūsu apekkhaṃ karissati, marissateva;"
msgstr "Whether or not you are concerned for your mother and father,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.7"
msgid "no cepāyasmā mātāpitūsu apekkhaṃ karissati, marissateva."
msgstr "you will die anyway."

msgctxt "sn55.54:3.8"
msgid "Sādhāyasmā, yā te mātāpitūsu apekkhā taṃ pajahā’ti."
msgstr "It would be good to give up concern for your mother and father.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:4.1"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.2"
msgid "‘yā me mātāpitūsu apekkhā sā pahīnā’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I have given up concern for my mother and father,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.3"
msgid "‘atthi panāyasmato puttadāresu apekkhā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But are you concerned for your partners and children?’"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.4"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.5"
msgid "‘atthi me puttadāresu apekkhā’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I am,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.6"
msgid "‘āyasmā kho māriso maraṇadhammo."
msgstr "‘But sir, it’s your nature to die."

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.7"
msgid "Sacepāyasmā puttadāresu apekkhaṃ karissati, marissateva;"
msgstr "Whether or not you are concerned for your partners and children,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.8"
msgid "no cepāyasmā puttadāresu apekkhaṃ karissati, marissateva."
msgstr "you will die anyway."

msgctxt "sn55.54:4.9"
msgid "Sādhāyasmā, yā te puttadāresu apekkhā taṃ pajahā’ti."
msgstr "It would be good to give up concern for your partners and children.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:5.1"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:5.2"
msgid "‘yā me puttadāresu apekkhā sā pahīnā’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""
"‘I have given up concern for my partners and children,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:5.3"
msgid "‘atthi panāyasmato mānusakesu pañcasu kāmaguṇesu apekkhā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘But are you concerned for the five kinds of human sensual stimulation?’"

msgctxt "sn55.54:5.4"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘atthi me mānusakesu pañcasu kāmaguṇesu apekkhā’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I am,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:5.6"
msgid ""
"‘mānusakehi kho, āvuso, kāmehi dibbā kāmā abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā ca."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sir, heavenly sensual pleasures are better than human sensual "
"pleasures."

#. VAR: cātumahārājikesu → cātummahārājikesu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.54:5.7"
msgid ""
"Sādhāyasmā, mānusakehi kāmehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā cātumahārājikesu devesu "
"cittaṃ adhimocehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"It would be good to turn your mind away from human sensual pleasures and fix "
"it on the gods of the Four Great Kings.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.410"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:6.1"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘mānusakehi me kāmehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ, cātumahārājikesu devesu cittaṃ "
"adhimocitan’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I have done so,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘cātumahārājikehi kho, āvuso, devehi tāvatiṃsā devā abhikkantatarā ca "
"paṇītatarā ca."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sir, the gods of the Thirty Three are better than the gods of the Four "
"Great Kings …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:6.4"
msgid ""
"Sādhāyasmā, cātumahārājikehi devehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā tāvatiṃsesu devesu "
"cittaṃ adhimocehī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:7.1"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘cātumahārājikehi me devehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ, tāvatiṃsesu devesu cittaṃ "
"adhimocitan’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.3"
msgid "‘tāvatiṃsehi kho, āvuso, devehi yāmā devā … pe …"
msgstr "Good sir, the gods of Yāma …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.4"
msgid "tusitā devā … pe …"
msgstr "the Joyful Gods …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.5"
msgid "nimmānaratī devā … pe …"
msgstr "the Gods Who Love to Create …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.6"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī devā … pe …"
msgstr "the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others …"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.7"
msgid ""
"paranimmitavasavattīhi kho, āvuso, devehi brahmaloko abhikkantataro ca "
"paṇītataro ca."
msgstr ""
"the Gods of the Brahmā realm are better than the Gods Who Control the "
"Creations of Others."

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.8"
msgid ""
"Sādhāyasmā, paranimmitavasavattīhi devehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā brahmaloke "
"cittaṃ adhimocehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"It would be good to turn your mind away from the Gods Who Control the "
"Creations of Others and fix it on the Gods of the Brahmā realm.’"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.9"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.10"
msgid ""
"‘paranimmitavasavattīhi me devehi cittaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ, brahmaloke cittaṃ "
"adhimocitan’ti, so evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "‘I have done so,’ they should say:"

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.11"
msgid "‘brahmalokopi kho, āvuso, anicco addhuvo sakkāyapariyāpanno."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sir, the Brahmā realm is impermanent, not lasting, and included within "
"identity."

msgctxt "sn55.54:7.12"
msgid ""
"Sādhāyasmā, brahmalokā cittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ "
"upasaṃharāhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"It would be good to turn your mind away from the Brahmā realm and apply it "
"to the cessation of identity.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.54:8.1"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If they reply,"

#. VAR: upasaṃharāmī’ti → upasaṃhatanti (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn55.54:8.2"
msgid "‘brahmalokā me cittaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ, sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ upasaṃharāmī’ti;"
msgstr "‘I have done so,’"

# See BB’s note on readings. I differ in choosing the reading asava vimuttacittena, as I can’t see what relevance the period of time has.
#. VAR: āsavā → vassasata (bj, s1, s2) | vassasataṃ (s3)
msgctxt "sn55.54:8.3"
msgid ""
"evaṃ vimuttacittassa kho, mahānāma, upāsakassa āsavā vimuttacittena "
"bhikkhunā na kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"then there is no difference between a lay follower whose mind is freed in "
"this way and a mendicant whose mind is freed from defilements; that is,"

msgctxt "sn55.54:8.4"
msgid "vimuttiyā vimuttan”ti."
msgstr "between the freedom of one and the other.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.54:8.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
